Key Features
Excellent hysteroscopy text that aims to meticulously cover the role of hysteroscopy, both diagnostic and therapeutic in clinical gynecology and infertility practice
Section that offers crucial, practical information on the hysteroscope and other related additional equipment
Chapters are relevant, complete, and easy-to-understand procedures are described in detail and fully illustrated with color photographs
Step-by-step descriptions of common operative surgical techniques and practical hints on hysteroscopy procedures
Complications are highlighted with authoritative guidance on how to avoid and manage them
Technical edge over other texts on this subject, written by internationally respected professionals Provides solid grounding in the art and science of hysteroscopy
Strongly recommended for all gynecologists in training and also to those in practice.
